\series bold
\lang english
Network Administrator
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall provide domain-specific technical analysis for network-related incidents as delegated by the Incident Commander.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall not exercise declaration authority by virtue of delegated analysis responsibility alone;
 declaration authority remains with the IT Director,
 the Assistant IT Director,
 or a Tier L3+ technical lead designated in writing by the IT Director per 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Systems Administrator
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall provide domain-specific technical analysis for server and endpoint-related incidents as delegated by the Incident Commander.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall not exercise declaration authority by virtue of delegated analysis responsibility alone;
 declaration authority remains with the IT Director,
 the Assistant IT Director,
 or a Tier L3+ technical lead designated in writing by the IT Director per 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
All Information Operations Personnel
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall create a Safety and Security category work order in the System of Engagement immediately upon discovery of any condition that may constitute an IoC,
 without exception.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall create Safety and Security work orders on behalf of external reporters —
 including vendors,
 end-users,
 and members of the public —
 documenting the reporting party as the source.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall not perform any response activity on a suspected cybersecurity incident without an associated work order.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall maintain familiarity with Layer 1 IoC categories and the Layer 2 indicator artifact.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall treat uncertain conditions as IoCs and initiate intake,
 consistent with the false-positive-safe principle established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.06"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

