\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
4.
 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Compliance with this policy is mandatory for all Information Operations personnel,
 contractors,
 and vendors subject to ECIO governance,
 in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assessment
\series default
:
 Compliance with IoC list governance,
 intake and triage obligations,
 classification and documentation requirements,
 CJIS notification mechanics,
 and retention obligations shall be assessed through the internal audit and self-assessment procedures defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Internal Audits and Self-Assessment Procedures) and the annual policy review and maturity scoring process defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Annual Policy Review and Maturity Scoring).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Enforcement
\series default
:
 Failure to create required work orders,
 failure to perform IoC evaluation before other response activity,
 failure to document declaration or decline with its basis,
 failure to execute CJIS notification within the windows established in Section 6.6,
 or failure to maintain required retention obligations,
 without documented justification,
 shall be treated as non-compliance and may result in corrective action under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exceptions
\series default
:
 Exceptions to any requirement of this policy shall be documented in writing with a business justification and approved by the IT Director in advance in accordance with the exception framework established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 within the delegation constraints of 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 No exception shall be granted on an open-ended basis;
 each exception shall specify a defined remediation timeline and any compensating measures in effect during the exception period.
 No exception may suspend or modify the CJIS notification obligations established in Section 6.6.
\end_layout

