\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4 Incident Record Structure
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The incident record for all declared Chapter 4 incidents shall use the existing work order infrastructure within the System of Engagement,
 supplemented by the mandatory Chapter 4 checklist template.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Work Order Infrastructure:
\series default

 The following existing work order fields constitute the structural foundation of the incident record:
 Subject,
 Description,
 Category (Safety and Security),
 Assignee,
 Notes,
 Files,
 Related Issues,
 Watchers,
 and operational Severity.
 The IT Director shall not modify these fields for Chapter 4 intake purposes.
 The system-generated audit trail within the System of Engagement provides the timestamped record for all status changes,
 field modifications,
 and note additions.
 This trail is tamper-evident and constitutes the authoritative chronological record of the incident.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Chapter 4 Checklist Template:
\series default

 The Assistant IT Director shall maintain a Chapter 4 checklist template as a governed Knowledge Base artifact per 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
