\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Incident Commander shall classify all declared Chapter 4 incidents on two (2) independent dimensions.
 Both shall be documented in the Chapter 4 checklist.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Incident Type:
\series default

 Incident type is determined by the applicable Layer 1 category or categories (A through F) and answers what kind of incident is being handled.
 An incident may carry multiple type classifications if it spans multiple categories.
 The IT Director or the Assistant IT Director shall document incident type at declaration.
 The Incident Commander may update incident type as investigation unfolds and shall document any update in the work order Notes with the basis for the change.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Incident Severity:
\series default

 Incident severity is determined using the three-tier framework established in 
\series bold
Policy 
